    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-05-11T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-05-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="126"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d126">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 893.51/415.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State of the American
                            Ambassador</gloss> to <gloss type="to">Japan</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Extract.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-05-11">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 11, 1911</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Referring to Department’s April 29,<note n="1" xml:id="d126fn1">Not
                        printed.</note> in which it was stated that the question of Japanese
                    participation finally rests with the financial groups, it may be added that in
                    case Japan should apply for participation on an equal footing with others not
                    now parties to the London agreement of April 15, the Department would be
                    prepared to support such an application.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Knox</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
